# SLAM
Service for storing and calculating SLA for various services

# Events
Incoming events

## Event Collection [/event]
### List all Incidents [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [{
            "id": 1,
            "failing_metrics_count": number,
            "service_id": number,
            "start": "datetime",
            "end": "datetime/null"
        }]

### Send an Event [POST]
Send an event to either trigger an Incident, add more failing metrics or resolve an Incident. Response will containt a list of updated incidents. 
+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "event_type": "trigger/resolve",
            "metric_id": "text",
            "sc_ids": [number, number],
            "created": "TIMESTAMP"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            [
                {
                    "id": number, 
                    "start": "datetime", 
                    "end": "datetime/null", 
                    "service_id": number, 
                    "failing_metrics_count": number
                }, 
                {
                    "id": number, 
                    "start": "datetime", 
                    "end": "datetime/null", 
                    "service_id": number, 
                    "failing_metrics_count": number
                }
            ]



## Event [/event/{id}]
A single Incident with all its details

+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Event to perform action with. Has example value.

+ Model (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "failing_metrics": [
                        {
                            "id": number, 
                            "metric_id": "text", 
                            "start": "datetime", 
                            "end": "datetime/null"
                        }
                    ],
                "service_id": number,
                "start": "datetime",
                "end": "datetime/null"
            }

### Retrieve an Event [GET]
+ Response 200

    [Event][]

